headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 27 of his career-high-matching 38 points in the second half as the Orlando Magic defeated the Detroit Pistons 111-99 for their third straight win on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner dominates second half as Magic pulls away to beat Pistons 111-99

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored a season-high 43 points in his return to Washington and the Phoenix Suns routed the Wizards 140-112 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bradley Beal scores 43 points in return to Washington as Suns roll past Wizards, 140-112

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 34 points before sitting out the final quarter and the NBA-leading Boston Celtics cruised to a 131-91 victory over the injury-depleted Memphis Grizzlies on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum scores 34 points to lead Celtics past short-handed Grizzlies, 131-91

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 25 points, nine assists and eight rebounds and the Indiana Pacers overcame a career-high 35 points from Hornets rookie Brandon Miller to beat Charlotte 115-99 on Sunday night and snap a three-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers overcome career-high 35 points from Brandon Miller to beat Hornets 115-99

headlines.description: — The Los Angeles Clippers have been on the road for nearly two weeks, forced from their home building because of the Grammy Awards.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kawhi Leonard scores 25, Clippers top Heat 103-95 for 25th win in last 30 games

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 22 of his 32 points in the third quarter, Rudy Gobert had 17 points and 13 rebounds and the Minnesota Timberwolves pulled away in the second half to beat the Houston Rockets 111-90 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 32 as Timberwolves pull away to beat Rockets 111-90

events.name: Toronto Raptors at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Josh Giddey scored 24 points, Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 23 and the Oklahoma City Thunder overcame a 23-point deficit to beat the Toronto Raptors 135-127 in double-overtime Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder overcome 23-point deficit to beat Raptors 135-127 in double-overtime

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen scored 21 points to lead the Utah Jazz to a 123-108 victory over the Milwaukee Bucks on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen scores 21, Jazz rally in fourth quarter to beat Bucks 123-108

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray loves that the Denver Nuggets can turn to their championship mettle in crunch time. He hates that they have to rely on that so often.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic and Murray lead Denver's comeback as Nuggets beat Blazers 112-103 for weekend sweep of rivals
